   <ab type="translation"
       xml:id="p0016_translation"
       corresp="#p0016_transcription"> <!-- starts on previous page --> despise not our petitions in our necessities, 
   	but deliver us always from all dangers, O blessed Virgin. <!-- the 'sub tuum praesidium' usually says 'o glorious and blessed' -->
   	Versicle. After childbirth
   	you remained a virgin; O mother of God, intercede for
   	us. Let us pray. Defend Thy servants, O Lord, by granting them the 
   	gift of peace, and as they have confidence in the patronage of 
   	Blessed Mary, ever Virgin, so do Thou
   	make them safe from all their enemies. Through Christ our Lord. Antiphon. Great Father, Saint Dominic, when our last hour arrives,
   	welcome us above, and ever watch over
   	us here below. Versicle. The mouth of
   	the just man shall
   	speak wisdom and his tongue shall utter judgement. <!-- continues to next page (Little Office BVM p 190) --> </ab>

